--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

MUST: `baseline-report.md` documenting stage-by-stage pass/fail, actual route counts, and the current WEIGHTS dict MUST be committed before this task is marked done.
MUST: `review.md` following the Curation Review Protocol structure MUST be committed with a verdict of PASS or PASS WITH ISSUES before this task is marked done.
MUST: `baseline/catalog.jsonl`, `baseline/scores.json`, `baseline/archetype_counts.json`, and `baseline/source_counts.json` MUST all be committed as the Epic 2 reference baseline.
MUST: `temperature=0` MUST be confirmed in the Haiku extraction logs and recorded in `baseline-report.md`.
MUST: Any bug discovered in existing pipeline code during validation MUST be fixed in-place under the Boy Scout rule; each fix MUST be committed separately with the commit SHA recorded in `baseline-report.md`.
NEVER: Push routes to the production Convex deployment — `convex_push.py` MUST only be invoked with the `--dry-run` flag in this task.
NEVER: Skip a pipeline stage even if a prior stage produced warnings or lower-than-expected counts — record the warning in `baseline-report.md` and continue.
NEVER: Refactor or restructure existing pipeline code for aesthetic or architectural reasons — this task is pure validation; only Boy Scout bug fixes are permitted.
STRICTLY: Limit Haiku extraction to a 20-route sample for cost control — do not run extraction over the full corpus in this task.
STRICTLY: Use the review.md verdict convention: PASS | PASS WITH ISSUES | FAIL — if the honest verdict would be FAIL, stop and escalate to the user rather than marking the task done.
STRICTLY: Document all N/A Curation Review Protocol steps (3-5, 9-11, 13) in `review.md` with the note "N/A until Epic X" so the review lineage is complete.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SPECIFICATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Objective:** Execute every existing curation pipeline stage (FHWA, MotorcycleRoads, BestBikingRoads scrapers → Haiku extraction sample → composite scoring → archetype classification → OSM enrichment → Convex push dry-run) against live sources and the dev Convex deployment, running the Curation Review Protocol first full run (Epic 2 steps: 1, 2, 6, 7, 8, 12), fixing any bugs discovered along the way, and committing the resulting baseline artifacts as the reference point for all subsequent hardening epics.

**Success looks like:** `baseline/catalog.jsonl` exists with a meaningful route count, each of the eight pipeline stages ran without crashes against live data, `baseline-report.md` documents stage-by-stage results with actual counts and the current WEIGHTS dict, `review.md` verdict is PASS or PASS WITH ISSUES with rationale, landmark spot checks (Tail of the Dragon, Blue Ridge Parkway, Beartooth Highway, Pacific Coast Highway, Million Dollar Highway) each appear once with expected archetype and scores, the Convex push dry-run completes without type errors, and all baseline artifacts are committed to the repository.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BACKGROUND
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

**Problem:** The curation pipeline at `scripts/curation/pipeline/` was built and unit-tested in isolation, but it has never been run end-to-end against live sources or the dev Convex deployment — no one knows whether all stages compose correctly, whether the current WEIGHTS are reasonable, whether the archetype distribution is sensible, or whether the Convex push serialization is type-safe.

**Why it matters:** Every subsequent hardening epic (INF-001 dependency install, Haiku calibration, OSM enrichment hardening, Convex schema evolution, quality scoring) assumes the baseline pipeline is functional. Layering hardening on top of a broken baseline wastes multiple epics of effort and produces a false confidence that the pipeline is progressing when it may have fundamental defects. The baseline must be proven before any extension is attempted.

**Current state:** The pipeline has source scrapers (`sources/fhwa.py`, `sources/motorcycleroads.py`, `sources/bestbikingroads.py`), Haiku extraction (`extraction/client.py` — Anthropic Instructor), composite scoring with a WEIGHTS dict (`scoring/composite.py`), archetype classification with 6 archetypes (`classification/archetype.py`), OSM enrichment via Overpass API with a disk cache (`enrichment/osm_client.py` + `enrichment/cache.py`), and a Convex push module with a `--dry-run` flag (`sync/convex_push.py`) — all written and individually testable, but never composed into a single end-to-end run. No baseline artifacts exist.

**Desired state:** All pipeline stages have been executed sequentially against live infrastructure; stage-by-stage counts and any discovered bugs are recorded in `baseline-report.md`; the Curation Review Protocol first full run is documented in `review.md` with a PASS verdict; and the `baseline/` directory contains the reference artifacts (`catalog.jsonl`, `scores.json`, `archetype_counts.json`, `source_counts.json`) that all future epics will diff against.

