ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA (TDD Beads)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Each AC is a RED → GREEN → REFACTOR micro-cycle for a pipeline stage validation.
Orchestrator advances through ACs sequentially.

AC-1: FHWA ingestion produces JSONL staging file with ~184 routes
  GIVEN: The FHWA pipeline module is installed with dependencies and network access to the FHWA byways data source is available
  WHEN: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.sources.fhwa` is executed
  THEN: A JSONL staging file is written containing between 165 and 203 route records (±10% of 184), each record having non-null name, state, and centroid coordinate fields; the module exits 0; the file path and count are recorded in `baseline-report.md`

  TDD_STATE: [ ] RED  [ ] VERIFY_RED  [ ] GREEN  [ ] VERIFY_GREEN  [ ] REFACTOR
  TEST_FILE: (validation recorded in baseline-report.md — no unit test)
  TEST_FUNCTION: verify_fhwa_ingestion
  VERIFY: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.sources.fhwa && FHWA_FILE=$(python -c "from scripts.curation.pipeline.sources.fhwa import OUTPUT_PATH; print(OUTPUT_PATH)") && COUNT=$(wc -l < "$FHWA_FILE") && echo "FHWA count: $COUNT" && python -c "import json; lines=[json.loads(l) for l in open('$FHWA_FILE')]; assert all('name' in r and 'state' in r for r in lines), 'Missing name/state'; print('FHWA AC-1 PASS')"`

AC-2: MotorcycleRoads and BestBikingRoads scrapers produce JSONL with reasonable counts
  GIVEN: robots.txt enforcement and rate limiting are active in the scraper base class and network access to motorcycleroads.com and bestbikingroads.com is available
  WHEN: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.sources.motorcycleroads` and `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.sources.bestbikingroads` are each executed sequentially
  THEN: MotorcycleRoads produces a JSONL file with more than 50 routes; BestBikingRoads produces a JSONL file with between 10,000 and 20,000 routes; both modules exit 0 without crashes; robots.txt compliance and rate-limit behavior are confirmed in logs; both counts are recorded in `baseline-report.md`

  TDD_STATE: [ ] RED  [ ] VERIFY_RED  [ ] GREEN  [ ] VERIFY_GREEN  [ ] REFACTOR
  TEST_FILE: (validation recorded in baseline-report.md)
  TEST_FUNCTION: verify_community_scrapers
  VERIFY: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.sources.motorcycleroads && python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.sources.bestbikingroads && python -c "import subprocess; mr=int(subprocess.check_output(['wc','-l','staging/motorcycleroads.jsonl']).split()[0]); bbr=int(subprocess.check_output(['wc','-l','staging/bestbikingroads.jsonl']).split()[0]); assert mr > 50, f'MR count {mr} < 50'; assert 10000 <= bbr <= 20000, f'BBR count {bbr} out of range'; print(f'AC-2 PASS: MR={mr} BBR={bbr}')"`

AC-3: Haiku extraction on 20-route sample produces fully-populated RouteAttributes
  GIVEN: A 20-route sample has been drawn from the FHWA staging JSONL and the `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable is set
  WHEN: The Haiku extraction client is invoked on the 20-route sample
  THEN: Each of the 20 routes receives a `RouteAttributes` object with `curvature_score`, `scenery_score`, `traffic_level`, `surface_condition`, and `elevation_change` all populated (non-null); `temperature=0` is present in the extraction log; `EXTRACTION_SCHEMA_VERSION` is logged once per batch; the 20 extracted objects are written to `baseline/catalog.jsonl`

  TDD_STATE: [ ] RED  [ ] VERIFY_RED  [ ] GREEN  [ ] VERIFY_GREEN  [ ] REFACTOR
  TEST_FILE: (validation recorded in baseline-report.md)
  TEST_FUNCTION: verify_haiku_extraction
  VERIFY: `python -c "import json; records=[json.loads(l) for l in open('.spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/baseline/catalog.jsonl')]; required=['curvature_score','scenery_score','traffic_level','surface_condition','elevation_change']; missing=[f for r in records for f in required if f not in r or r[f] is None]; assert len(missing)==0, f'Missing fields: {missing}'; assert len(records)==20, f'Expected 20, got {len(records)}'; print('AC-3 PASS')" && grep -q 'temperature.*0' .spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/baseline-report.md && grep -q 'EXTRACTION_SCHEMA_VERSION' .spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/baseline-report.md`

AC-4: Composite scoring produces valid floats and WEIGHTS dict is captured
  GIVEN: The 20 extracted `RouteAttributes` from AC-3 are available as input
  WHEN: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.scoring.composite` is run on the extracted sample
  THEN: `composite_score`, `curvature_score`, `scenic_score`, and any other dimension scores are all floats in `[0.0, 1.0]`; no route has a null or NaN score; the WEIGHTS dict from `scoring/composite.py` is logged and captured verbatim in `baseline-report.md`; scored routes are written to `baseline/scores.json`

  TDD_STATE: [ ] RED  [ ] VERIFY_RED  [ ] GREEN  [ ] VERIFY_GREEN  [ ] REFACTOR
  TEST_FILE: (validation recorded in baseline-report.md)
  TEST_FUNCTION: verify_composite_scoring
  VERIFY: `python -c "import json; data=json.load(open('.spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/baseline/scores.json')); assert all(isinstance(r.get('composite_score'),float) and 0.0<=r['composite_score']<=1.0 for r in data), 'composite_score out of range'; print(f'AC-4 PASS: {len(data)} routes scored')" && grep -q 'WEIGHTS' .spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/baseline-report.md`

AC-5: Archetype classifier assigns one of 6 valid archetypes to every scored route
  GIVEN: The scored routes from AC-4 are available as input
  WHEN: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.classification.archetype` is run on the scored sample
  THEN: Every route has a `primary_archetype` value that is exactly one of `twisties`, `mountain`, `coastal`, `adventure`, `scenic_byway`, `desert`; every route has a `secondary_tags` field that is a list (may be empty); no route has a null `primary_archetype`; archetype distribution counts are written to `baseline/archetype_counts.json`

  TDD_STATE: [ ] RED  [ ] VERIFY_RED  [ ] GREEN  [ ] VERIFY_GREEN  [ ] REFACTOR
  TEST_FILE: (validation recorded in baseline-report.md)
  TEST_FUNCTION: verify_archetype_classification
  VERIFY: `python -c "import json; VALID={'twisties','mountain','coastal','adventure','scenic_byway','desert'}; data=json.load(open('.spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/baseline/archetype_counts.json')); keys=set(data.keys()); assert keys.issubset(VALID), f'Invalid archetypes: {keys-VALID}'; print(f'AC-5 PASS: archetypes={data}')"`

AC-6: OSM enrichment populates surface/smoothness/curvature and cache hit confirmed on second run
  GIVEN: A 10-route sample is available and the OSM disk cache directory exists (or is created on first run)
  WHEN: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.enrichment.osm_client` is run on the 10-route sample twice in sequence
  THEN: The first run populates `surface`, `smoothness`, and `curvature` fields on all 10 routes via live Overpass API calls; the second run retrieves all 10 routes from the disk cache without making live API calls; `cache_hit_rate` of 100% is logged on the second run; both runs exit 0

  TDD_STATE: [ ] RED  [ ] VERIFY_RED  [ ] GREEN  [ ] VERIFY_GREEN  [ ] REFACTOR
  TEST_FILE: (validation recorded in baseline-report.md)
  TEST_FUNCTION: verify_osm_enrichment
  VERIFY: `python -c "import json; records=[json.loads(l) for l in open('.spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/baseline/catalog.jsonl')]; enriched=[r for r in records if r.get('osm_surface') is not None]; assert len(enriched)>=10, f'Only {len(enriched)} routes have OSM data'; print(f'AC-6 PASS: {len(enriched)} routes enriched')" && grep -q 'cache_hit_rate' .spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/baseline-report.md`

AC-7: Convex push dry-run completes without type errors and serialized payload is logged
  GIVEN: The dev Convex deployment is reachable (VAL-004 dependency satisfied) and `convex_push.py` supports a `--dry-run` flag
  WHEN: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.sync.convex_push --dry-run` is executed against the baseline sample
  THEN: The module exits 0; no `TypeError` or `ValidationError` appears in stdout/stderr; the batch upsert payload is serialized and logged; the logged payload structure is captured in `baseline-report.md`; NO routes are written to the production deployment

  TDD_STATE: [ ] RED  [ ] VERIFY_RED  [ ] GREEN  [ ] VERIFY_GREEN  [ ] REFACTOR
  TEST_FILE: (validation recorded in baseline-report.md)
  TEST_FUNCTION: verify_convex_push_dryrun
  VERIFY: `python -m scripts.curation.pipeline.sync.convex_push --dry-run 2>&1 | tee /tmp/convex_dryrun.log; RC=$?; test $RC -eq 0 && grep -qi 'TypeError\|ValidationError\|traceback' /tmp/convex_dryrun.log && echo 'FAIL' && exit 1 || echo 'AC-7 PASS: no type errors, exit 0'`

AC-8: All baseline artifacts committed and review.md verdict is PASS or PASS WITH ISSUES
  GIVEN: All prior ACs (1-7) have been validated and baseline artifacts written
  WHEN: `git log` and `git diff` are inspected after the final commit
  THEN: `git log` shows at least one commit containing `baseline-report.md`, `review.md`, `baseline/catalog.jsonl`, `baseline/scores.json`, `baseline/archetype_counts.json`, and `baseline/source_counts.json`; `review.md` contains `Verdict: PASS` (or `PASS WITH ISSUES`) on its verdict line; `review.md` documents N/A steps 3-5, 9-11, 13 with "N/A until Epic X" notes; any bug-fix commits have their SHA recorded in `baseline-report.md`

  TDD_STATE: [ ] RED  [ ] VERIFY_RED  [ ] GREEN  [ ] VERIFY_GREEN  [ ] REFACTOR
  TEST_FILE: (validation recorded in baseline-report.md)
  TEST_FUNCTION: verify_baseline_committed
  VERIFY: `for f in baseline-report.md review.md baseline/catalog.jsonl baseline/scores.json baseline/archetype_counts.json baseline/source_counts.json; do git ls-files --error-unmatch ".spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/$f" || { echo "MISSING from git: $f"; exit 1; }; done && grep -E '^Verdict: PASS' .spec/prds/curation-hardening/tasks/epic-02-baseline-pipeline-validation/review.md && echo 'AC-8 PASS'`

