NOTES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- This is the first end-to-end run of the curation pipeline. Expect to encounter at least minor bugs (missing `__main__` guards, hardcoded relative paths, missing `OUTPUT_PATH` constants). Fix them under the Boy Scout rule and commit each fix separately.
- The 20-route extraction sample should use a fixed random seed (e.g., `seed=42`) for reproducibility. Document the seed and sample selection method in `baseline-report.md`.
- If any landmark route (Tail of the Dragon, Blue Ridge Parkway, Beartooth Highway, Pacific Coast Highway, Million Dollar Highway) is missing from the FHWA source, this is expected to be a PASS WITH ISSUES not a FAIL — FHWA coverage is known to be incomplete.
- `baseline-report.md` should include a table with columns: `Stage | Status | Count | Notes`. This table is the primary artifact future engineers will reference.
- `review.md` N/A section must explicitly enumerate steps 3 (HPMS enrichment), 4 (NWS enrichment), 5 (HPMS+NWS quality gate), 9 (calibration gate), 10 (calibration tuning), 11 (field validation), 13 (hardened push) as "N/A until Epic X" with the appropriate epic number.
- The OSM cache directory path should be confirmed by reading `enrichment/cache.py` before the first run. If the cache path is relative, it may resolve differently depending on the working directory — fix this under Boy Scout rule if needed.
- Do not run BestBikingRoads full scrape if it will take more than 60 minutes — if the scraper lacks a `--max-pages` flag, add one as a Boy Scout fix and run with a bounded sample that still exceeds 50 routes, documenting the decision in `baseline-report.md`.

